        <div class="text-contents d-flex gap-3 flex-column"><h2 class="h2-big">How Does a Virtual Orthopedic Appointment Work?</h2><p>A virtual orthopedic appointment, also known as a telemedicine visit, simplifies the process of receiving specialist care by using video call technology for direct communication between patients and one of our orthopedic specialists, such as Dr. Lawyer. This method facilitates a thorough discussion regarding symptoms, medical history, and allows a specialist to perform a remote evaluation of your condition.</p>
<p>To maximize the effectiveness of your virtual consultation, it's important to have a reliable internet connection and a device with a camera and microphone ready. Before your appointment, we advise gathering and submitting any relevant medical documents or imaging results, like x-rays or MRIs, to make sure we have a comprehensive understanding of your condition. This preparation helps ensure a more accurate assessment and enhances the virtual consultation experience, making it as close to an in-office visit as possible.</p><a href="#" class="btn btn-card mt-0">Cartilage Regeneration Therapy & Repair</a></div>
